        YOU_GOT_GUTS_TO_COME_TO_THIS_NECK                                    = 7559,  -- You got guts to come to this neck of the woods. I can see you ain't no ordinary adventurer, but you ain't the best yet, neither. Don't get your feathers ruffled, I just tell it like it is.
        ME_I_M_A_BLACKSMITH_AND_A_DAMN                                       = 7560,  -- Me, I'm a blacksmith, and a damn good one. My Goblin forgecraft can make the most worthless rusty piece of junk shine like new again. Looks like you take good care of your weapons, though.
        YOU_GOT_NOTHING_FOR_ME_TO_WORK_ON                                    = 7561,  -- You got nothing for me to work on, so this conversation is over. I got better things to do than sit here and waste time trading insults with smart-alecky adventurers. Bye-bye now.
        HOLD_IT_RIGHT_THERE_PAL_IS_THAT_YOU                                  = 7562,  -- Hold it right there, pal! Is that % you're carrying? The power hidden behind that worn appearance is making my old Gobbie ears twitch. Trust me, I'm a blacksmith. I don't kid around when it comes to weapons.
        HRMMM_IT_D_TAKE_A_LOTTA_WORK_BUT                                     = 7563,  -- Hrmmm. It'd take a lotta work, but I could make that power shine through again. Okay, adventure-boy/adventure-girl], you got something to write with?
        TO_REFORGE_THE_I_M_GONNA_NEED_AND                                    = 7564,  -- To reforge the %, I'm gonna need %, %, and %. Yep, that's the bare minimum.
        BRING_ALONG_THE_WITH_THOSE_THREE_ITEMS_AND                           = 7565,  -- Bring along the % with those three items and I'll get to work for you. I've told you what I need, the rest is up to you.
        YOU_GOT_ME_WHAT_I_NEED_LEMME_SEE                                     = 7566,  -- You got me what I need? Lemme see here, %, %, and %. Good work. Did I mention that I don't work for free? I'm gonna need a little something up front--don't trust you sneaky adventurer-types.
        OH_AND_I_GOT_NO_INTEREST_IN_GIL                                      = 7567,  -- Oh, and I got no interest in gil. My fee for this job is # . You people pay each other for stuff all the time, right? Well, this ain't no different. You pay my fee, your weapon gets fixed up.
        REFORGING_THE_IS_GONNA_COST_YOU_YOU_PAY                              = 7568,  -- Reforging the % is gonna cost you # . You pay me and I start working. See you when you get back with my fee.
        YOU_BROUGHT_ME_MY_RIGHT_TIME_TO_GET                                  = 7569,  -- You brought me my # ? Right, time to get to work. My forge is hot and ready to go.
        THE_GOBLIN_WAY_OF_SMITHING_IS_A_LITTLE                               = 7570,  -- The Goblin way of smithing is a little different from your fancy-schmancy synthesis. I'm gonna need some time to get this job done. You kept me waiting for the materials I needed, now it's your turn to cool your heels for a while. Fair's fair, right?
        YOU_BACK_ALREADY_I_TOLD_YOU_THIS_WAS                                 = 7571,  -- You back already? I told you this was gonna take some time. You adventurer-types have really gotta learn some patience. Let me get back to work, will ya? Sheesh.
        YOU_CAN_STOP_YOUR_BELLYACHIN_NOW_I_M                                 = 7572,  -- You can stop your bellyachin' now--I'm done with your %. So what do you think? You ain't gonna see too many weapons of this quality, I can tell you. Be seeing you, adventure-boy/adventure-girl].
        OH_YEAH_ONE_MORE_THING_THE_I_WORKED                                  = 7573,  -- Oh yeah, one more thing: the % I worked on can still be improved. I can make that power shine even brighter than before. Do I have your full attention, now? Naturally, it's gonna cost you.
        THE_WEAPONS_YOU_PEOPLE_USE_ARE_REALLY_POPULAR                        = 7574,  -- The weapons you people use are really popular among the beastmen these days. I could make myself a small fortune with just a few of them.
        THE_TOP_SELLERS_AT_THE_MOMENT_ARE_AND                                = 7575,  -- The top sellers at the moment are %, %, and %. There are others I could think of, but those three bring in the most cash. Don't forget to bring the % back with you, too.
        THOSE_THREE_ITEMS_COVER_THE_COST_OF_MATERIALS                        = 7576,  -- Those three items cover the cost of materials for reforging the %, but I'm still gonna ask you for a separate fee for my sweat and toil. To forge, or not to forge? The answer is in your hands.
        OHO_YOU_BROUGHT_ME_WHAT_I_ASKED_FOR                                  = 7577,  -- Oho, you brought me what I asked for? %, %, and %. My pockets are gonna be bulging when I unload this stuff, heh heh.
        NOW_ABOUT_THAT_FEE_AS_A_CRAFTSGOBLIN_IT                              = 7578,  -- Now about that fee. As a craftsgoblin, it's embarrassin' to admit, but I don't think I can reforge the % for you. There's a blacksmith I know who can do the job, though. Damn expensive, but the best blacksmith I ever saw.
        THE_FEE_INCLUDING_MY_CUT_FOR_THE_REFERRAL                            = 7579,  -- The fee, including my cut for the referral, comes out to # . It's gonna be a fun time getting your grubby little adventurer hands on the loot, but the result will be worth it.
        I_DON_T_HAVE_THE_SKILL_TO_REFORGE                                    = 7580,  -- I don't have the skill to reforge the % you gave me, so I'm gonna take it to a blacksmith friend of mine. It'll be expensive, but the work is topnotch.
        THE_FEE_INCLUDING_MY_CUT_FOR_THE_REFERRAL_2                          = 7581,  -- The fee, including my cut for the referral, comes out to # . It's gonna be a fun time getting your grubby little adventurer hands on the loot, but the result will be worth it.
